docs.source: Recorded by Dave Cohen and Justin Lee 2 Nakamichi CM300 Omnis Spaced at 2 meters>Nakamichi 550 w/dolby B Maxell XLIIS90s cassettes 3/4 of the way back in OTS, DFC The Master Cassettes were played back with Azimuth adjustment and Dolby Decoded on a Nakamichi CD1 into a Korg MR1000 at DSF 1 bit 5.6MHz. Subsequent conversion to 24/96 AIFF done via Korg Audiogate software. Redbook CDR standard 16/44.1 files were created using Bias Peak, Izotope Ozone's MBIT+ (for all dithering), and Weiss Saracon SRC (all sample rate conversions). FLAC'd using Audiofile Engineering Sample Manager. Transfer by Dave Cohen

docs.description: Set 1 Bill warms up, chats Bill - Picasso Moon Bill chats with sound engineers Bill warms up, chats Bill take 1 - Blow Away Bill take 2 - Blow Away Bill take 3 - Blow Away Bill take 4 - Blow Away Bill take 5 - Blow Away Jerry tells Bill - Blow Away Bill take 6 - Blow Away Bill take 7 - Blow Away Jerry, Bill chat - Blow Away Set 2 Bob take 1 - Picasso Moon Bob brief break Bob take 2 - Picasso Moon Bob take 3 - Picasso Moon Bob take 4 - Picasso Moon Bob take 5 - Picasso Moon Bob take 6 - Picasso Moon Bob take 7 - Picasso Moon Bob take 8 - Picasso Moon Bob take 9 - Picasso Moon Bob stops Set 3 Jerry warms up Phil & Jerry warm up (Phil & Jerry warm up) (1) Bob, Jerry & Brent warm up (2) take 1 - Just A Little Light chat & warm up take 2 - Just A Little Light chat Set IV: (Phil, Bob, Jerry and Brent listen) take 3 - Just A Little Light take 4 - Just A Little Light chat about next rehearsal Set V: (Jerry only) Jerry practices more Jerry - Adams Family theme Jerry - Mr. Ed - more practice take 5 - Just A Little Light (3) closing chat (1) Phil not on video, audio only (2) Brent not on video, audio only (3) Jerry only slideshow (not on audio releases since it is silent video - this is the only compilation on the video) This is NOT a compilation. It is: The View from Club Front - The Making of Built to Last. It is actual footage of members of the band practicing and laying down tracks individually and at times 2, 3 or 4 of them together. Video exists AND audio is also separate. Excellent quality SBD audio as well as good video! THIS ALL APPEARS TO BE SHOT/RECORDED THE SAME DAY (except for the ending silent slideshow). Video Exists!
